  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.240" end="00:00:06.620" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors. This Adventure guide will
<br />cover table calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:06.620" end="00:00:09.400" tts:direction="ltr">one of my favorite features in Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:09.400" end="00:00:12.940" tts:direction="ltr">Let's jump right in to the topics that
<br />I'll cover.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:12.940" end="00:00:15.940" tts:direction="ltr">I'll first do a short overview of
<br />calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:15.940" end="00:00:20.380" tts:direction="ltr">and then we will dive into six different
<br />table calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:20.380" end="00:00:22.625" tts:direction="ltr">and you can see those right there.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:22.625" end="00:00:26.850" tts:direction="ltr">I wanted to let you know that for this
<br />next Karen,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.850" end="00:00:31.930" tts:direction="ltr">you will be asked to gather some insights
<br />using table calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:31.930" end="00:00:34.350" tts:direction="ltr">but I will focus on these three,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:34.350" end="00:00:38.410" tts:direction="ltr">the running total, the percent different,
<br />and the percent total.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:38.410" end="00:00:40.250" tts:direction="ltr">As you're watching this AG,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:40.250" end="00:00:42.070" tts:direction="ltr">just pay attention to those.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:42.070" end="00:00:47.230" tts:direction="ltr">I believe all of you will be able to
<br />easily perform table calculations.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:47.230" end="00:00:49.570" tts:direction="ltr">But just wanted to give you a heads up so
<br />that</p>
        <p begin="00:00:49.570" end="00:00:52.705" tts:direction="ltr">you weren't too overwhelmed by all six of
<br />them.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:52.705" end="00:00:54.860" tts:direction="ltr">Now, there are three different types of</p>
        <p begin="00:00:54.860" end="00:00:56.980" tts:direction="ltr">calculations that you can do in Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:56.980" end="00:00:59.060" tts:direction="ltr">The first is table calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:59.060" end="00:01:00.840" tts:direction="ltr">which we'll do in this AG,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:00.840" end="00:01:06.520" tts:direction="ltr">and those only transform values at the
<br />level of detail on the worksheet.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:06.520" end="00:01:08.680" tts:direction="ltr">We will see that in just a moment,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:08.680" end="00:01:12.320" tts:direction="ltr">but you are not adding anything to the
<br />data source.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:12.320" end="00:01:14.420" tts:direction="ltr">Whereas in basic calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:14.420" end="00:01:18.240" tts:direction="ltr">you're going to transform values at the
<br />data source level of detail.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:18.240" end="00:01:22.040" tts:direction="ltr">That means you're actually creating new
<br />fields of data,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:22.040" end="00:01:24.460" tts:direction="ltr">and that is very different because then</p>
        <p begin="00:01:24.460" end="00:01:27.730" tts:direction="ltr">those new fields can be applied to other
<br />worksheets.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:27.730" end="00:01:31.940" tts:direction="ltr">Then finally, we have LOD or level of
<br />detail expressions,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:31.940" end="00:01:36.200" tts:direction="ltr">and those are similar to basic
<br />calculations but allow more granularity
<br />and</p>
        <p begin="00:01:36.200" end="00:01:41.080" tts:direction="ltr">control and include the commands of
<br />include xclude and fixed.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:41.080" end="00:01:46.590" tts:direction="ltr">We won't be covering those in this course
<br />because we do cover them in 5,400.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:46.590" end="00:01:49.900" tts:direction="ltr">Okay. So to create an edit table
<br />calculations,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:49.900" end="00:01:52.700" tts:direction="ltr">you first need to have a measure on the
<br />view.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:52.700" end="00:01:54.740" tts:direction="ltr">You'll have to bring a measure onto the
<br />view</p>
        <p begin="00:01:54.740" end="00:01:57.260" tts:direction="ltr">and then you can select a drop down menu,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:57.260" end="00:02:03.580" tts:direction="ltr">and then you can select either a table
<br />calculation or an ad table calculation.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:03.580" end="00:02:06.800" tts:direction="ltr">Once you do that, you know that it's been
<br />applied when</p>
        <p begin="00:02:06.800" end="00:02:10.800" tts:direction="ltr">the Delta sign is in the pill. Okay.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:10.800" end="00:02:14.280" tts:direction="ltr">What are some examples of table
<br />calculations?</p>
        <p begin="00:02:14.280" end="00:02:19.240" tts:direction="ltr">Some of my favorite are running totals
<br />where I can see sales over time.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:19.240" end="00:02:22.060" tts:direction="ltr">We have difference, which is maybe
<br />something you would</p>
        <p begin="00:02:22.060" end="00:02:24.860" tts:direction="ltr">show difference in sales across quarters,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:24.860" end="00:02:27.520" tts:direction="ltr">or you have percent of total when</p>
        <p begin="00:02:27.520" end="00:02:32.040" tts:direction="ltr">maybe you have subcategories and you want
<br />to see how they break out.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:32.240" end="00:02:36.360" tts:direction="ltr">These are some previews of the six charts
<br />we'll be making.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:36.360" end="00:02:38.260" tts:direction="ltr">We're going to do a running total,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:38.260" end="00:02:41.660" tts:direction="ltr">a difference from a percent difference,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:41.660" end="00:02:46.320" tts:direction="ltr">a percent total, a moving average and a
<br />rank.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:46.320" end="00:02:51.220" tts:direction="ltr">I am super excited for you all to learn
<br />how to use tableClad calculation.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:51.220" end="00:02:53.700" tts:direction="ltr">Let's dive in. All right.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:53.700" end="00:02:57.460" tts:direction="ltr">You should be on the AG table COC start
<br />file,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:57.460" end="00:03:02.040" tts:direction="ltr">and I want to just give you a quick
<br />overview of the data that I'm using.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:02.040" end="00:03:03.820" tts:direction="ltr">Here in the left pane,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:03.820" end="00:03:07.420" tts:direction="ltr">you can see I've got a lot of different
<br />data sources.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:07.420" end="00:03:11.080" tts:direction="ltr">Now, each of these have been brought in
<br />separately through</p>
        <p begin="00:03:11.080" end="00:03:16.285" tts:direction="ltr">a data blend and there is no connection or
<br />relationship between any of them.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:16.285" end="00:03:19.090" tts:direction="ltr">That is a little bit of a tip if you</p>
        <p begin="00:03:19.090" end="00:03:22.970" tts:direction="ltr">have multiple data sources for your
<br />project,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:22.970" end="00:03:25.130" tts:direction="ltr">but they have no relationship,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:25.130" end="00:03:27.090" tts:direction="ltr">no need to union or join,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:27.090" end="00:03:30.390" tts:direction="ltr">you might want to bring them in as a data
<br />blend.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:30.390" end="00:03:33.770" tts:direction="ltr">You can do that by going into</p>
        <p begin="00:03:34.380" end="00:03:40.040" tts:direction="ltr">the data tab at the top and selecting new
<br />data source.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:40.040" end="00:03:43.000" tts:direction="ltr">Then you'll navigate to your data source,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:43.000" end="00:03:46.720" tts:direction="ltr">and it will come onto the data source
